comment:
I've worked with many domestic abuse cases and part of my job not to make judgement, i have also worked as an operator in the UK for many year (its 999 here), I have been on the phone many times for this type of case, where a friend or onlooker is calling on their behalf, and not just some but EVERY single call i dealt with from 2009-2018 (I'm now working full time in the BooBoo Bus :-) ) 
was always pretty much the same in terms of the callers emotions, they were always panicked, some of them got scared incase they got seen making the call and so on, but always worry in their voice, the odd few seemed to have anger in their voice but thats understandable.
Domestic abuse is an awful thing to go through, i hope non of you ever experience it EVER, but if you ever do then tell someone, even if its just the once their is no excuse for anyone to hurt you, you deserve better.

It's been a while since i've been an operator but 1 thing that always upset me, was how guys would call because of an abusive partner and they would sound ashamed, or say things like "I Bet you'd never heard of a girl hitting a guy before", to which i'd always say "You'd be suprised", I agree that it's uncommon to hear, but its not as uncommon as you might think, sadly many men feel shame in it and just don't say anything. it's nothing to be ashamed about at all, if your a victim that is, the abuser should be deeply ashamed as theirs no excuse for it.
I see many of my british and american brothers and sisters here in the comments,  also from around the world, i really hope non of you ever have to deal with this sort of thing, but if your going through it right now then please for your own sake tell someone, who ever it is does not deserve you in their life and you deserve so much better, I know it's easy for me to say remove them from your life, but they really do not deserve you, and you need to speak out, no matter what your circumstances are you need to remove this person/s from your life, don't put up with it, Just like our fellow human Mr Depp, You are the Star in your own story, if someone is poisoning your story with negativity like abuse then remove them from the plotline and youl soon find that the story becomes focused back on you, but only you can seek help, and i really hope you do if you need it.

but anyway, i hope i diddnt say anything that could offend anyone here, i know that from were im sitting i can't really help anyone but i hope that my comment inspires someone who needs help to go and get some. because again, you deserve it. 

Love from the north of England.

comment:
I want to thank you for the time and care you put into these videos. I can't imagine the work that goes into just one let alone multiple videos. You are very smart, the things you've picked up on are amazing. I feel horrible for Johnny. He even said in that one text I'm sad, I'm not angry. The media gets ahold of any story they can to get ratings they don't care about facts or potentially ruining someone's life as long as it sells. Johnny Depp is a human being and from what I've heard, he is a very kind, generous, good-hearted man. Not to many people have a bad word to say about him except for the obvious, AH stans, AH herself and her friends, which I can completely see sitting around laughing and coming up with their lies. Makes me sick. There are many videos of people he has worked with that have nothing but the kindest things to say about him. Not just his co-stars or Directors, everyone on set. He doesn't care if you're his producer or the craft service people. He just cares for people. I've heard many stories from his co-stars, who seem genuinely in awe of him. One of many, many stories is they all had just finished working a 14 hour shift and then he stood in the pouring rain for hours making sure every single person that came for an autograph got one. Unlike a lot of younger stars who honestly think they are above people that somehow their fame makes them better than us "normal" people. I won't name any names but there is one pop star that actually gets people to carry her around, that is just insane. A well known actress ( I've never understood the appeal about her at all) complains that being a famous Mom is so much more difficult than being a "regular" Mom. She was born rich, she's never had to watch her Dad work so hard, taking every overtime shift, often in the middle of the night. Having to start a sideline bussiness forming up concrete after working 8 hours, then using the weekends to pour and finish the concrete and still make it to your softball games. My point is Johnny Depp is not in the least bit entitled, he understands that he gets to do what he loves and makes a lot of money for it, he is so apperceive for what he has and why he has it. Of course because he's a very talented actor but more importantly he knows without his fans he wouldn't be able to do what he loves and he shows them his appreciation. I'm so sick of these young stars not willing to sign autographs at all. Johnny loves his fans and it shows. He dresses up as Captain Jack Sparrow and visits Children's hospitals. He doesn't stay 20 minutes for the publicity, he is known to stay at least 5 hours, trying to get to know as many children and families as he can. It breaks my heart to see anyone with such a good heart fall into the trap of a Narcissist. He said it perfectly in one of the audios, don't quote me, I get it now, talking to AH, you were never real, you were someone I made up in my head. So again I want to thank you for taking all of this time to put together the best, most thought out and accurate videos on this awful subject. It's about time the good guy got a win! ‚ù§
Sorry for the length of this post, obviously this is a subject I am very passionate about not only because I'm a fan but because of the complete injustice of it all. Not to mention, Women like her are the reason why a lot of real victims of DV are scared to speak up, in fear of no one believing them. That's the most discusting part of all of this.

comment: Not sure how it works in New York, but in California if you call 911 from a cellphone it goes straight to CHP. CHP then requires the incident address in order to forward the call to the proper agency the incident address is policed by. The only way to circumvent this is if you know/search the agencies dedicated 911 phone number, which is not the same as dialing 911. So if the friend in New York truly called 911 it would have gone to whatever agency in New York that is the domain for 911, they would've had to figure out which agency is over where the incident took place and forward from there causing a huge delay in time which is crucial in DV cases. So I'm sorry, but I don't believe the friend in New York was the one who called 911, I believe it was the one staying in the other penthouse, which makes more sense. Lying and ruining someone's career is not okay!

comment:
Not only does it sound odd that a call log would include the detail of HOW Amber was assaulted, but there's also a glaring seemingly HUMAN ERROR in the police call log that is supposed to be very much computer-generated. I suspect the paper where the iPhone is mentioned is entirely fake. Whether this is a tabloid illustration or actual evidence, I don't know, maybe you do.

In Io's logs, he made the calls to Amber at 11:11 pm NY time. However, in the "police call log" (video point 14:06) the call log reads in the 24-hour format 23:23. If this is supposed to match IOS  11:11 call, the 24-hour format should read 23:11, not 23:23. However, the 911 call, should, by the same logic be stamped at 23:16, not 23:23. Where did this "log" come from? Is this covering the fact the 911 call was a bit tardy, and to give a reason for the other "Lauren" call to be made? (Let's move Io's call up by a few minutes, if 23:23 would actually mean 11:11, then say "Lauren" made the second call.)

But I think IO got confused in her Tweet about which number is which. She called Raquel (LA) first and Austin Texas is Amber, not Raquel. But even then, that call lasts ONE MINUTE, and it was supposedly about the poop in the bed, and even Johnny says the call lasted a bit more than a minute, presumably. So did she cut out the part of the log that shows the ACTUAL call with Johnny, and the one-minute call is a plant for the logs? (Note that the computer listing is confused about the 3AM log that is put in the wrong order. Check the minutes rather than hours.) Did Amber fake the abuse call to make iO call the cops in good faith? Now she can't see how she's been fooled?

However, THIS recording you shared is the recording of the 911 call made after 10 pm (22:07) LA time, 1.5 hours after Johnny has left the building according to the surveillance video. (I can't remember the exact time.) So this is made by Raquel, then, not iO as I thought. So iO probably did call 911 straight away, but this is Raquel at 22:07 (Past 10 pm in LA).

There's a link to the call log for the Raquel's after ten call: https://images.app.goo.gl/da21Y8fYruyevFr26 (The mechanical voice keeps giving the 24 hour time in the background in case you didn't notice being used to the 12-hour clock.)

Whose hand-writing is that, you think, considering there WAS a call made at that hour.  I suspected a lawyer, but there's a call, this is not a "telecast", like they claimed to explain the delay... That the call was made 1.5 hours later because io was in NY and LAPD would take a long time to answer. So are they trying to narrow down the gap between the widely reported two calls, at the same time as to explain why there was two.

Curious.

comment:
Brian, I really hope you read this, because you really are doing something amazing, not only for J.D but society in general.

People like Amber are among us and unfortunately the people that have had to deal with them prefer being silent because:
 
1. Its painful, personal, and preferably a private issue. 
2. Most people find these kinds of schemes unbelievable because they are not something most people would do. 

But as a person that would never speak about my painful personal experiences, I was very much afraid I wouldn't learn from them. As I watched your videos, it was like therapy. You are not only vindicating johnny Depp, but a whole lot of people that have been manipulated, hurt, slandered and driven to despair by these kinds of people, the greatest part is that you are treating J.D with dignity and humanity, which alleviates the fear of people who don't want to be labeled as a broken person when they speak up about these kinds of situations. 


I always thought Johnny Depp was a great actor, but this ordeal made me have so much respect for him as a human being. I know he went through hell several times because of this mess, once privately and now when he has to basically show this mess to the whole world. But I hope he knows its helping people. I know that nothing will "fix" what happened, but at the very least I hope he knows I owe him gratitude for what he has contributed to my life personally, rather than just entertainment-wise. He shows us its possible to be redeemed, vindicated, and rise from the ashes, and its thanks to you that many of us can see that, so Thank you so so so much for what you are doing!

People of the comment section: although i think these videos are interesting and bring a lot of ideas and facts to light we shouldnt say vile things about the people involved. We do not know these people, if this is how it happened or if it did happen what the knowledge or motivations of these people may be. Yes, ask questions and try to learn what the truth is but be careful what you say considering the truth may not always be what we think it is.
